    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-01-07T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-01-07T14:00:00-05:00" n="423"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d423">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/1045: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-01-07T12:00:00-07:00"
                            >January 7, 1931—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 3:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. A coalition of the official Liberal and the Progresista sections of the
                    Liberal Party, under the name of the Liberal Progresista Party, has launched the
                    candidacy of General Jorge Ubico for President. The Independiente section of the
                    party under the leadership of Bernardo Alvarado Tello has refused to join this
                    coalition. Up to the present time there is no opposition candidate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
